textAfterTable: 2012-13 Season (Sophomore): Appeared in 25 games, starting one...Averaged 11.4 minutes per contest...Scored four points per game while shooting 49.2 percent (32-for-65) from the field...Averaged 2.8 rebounds per game...Dished out 17 assists and recorded 19 steals...Netted 12 points on 5-for-7 shooting and grabbed three rebounds against MSOE (Jan. 9)...Pulled down a season-best seven rebounds, while adding five points versus Maranatha Baptist Bible College (Dec. 8)...Scored seven points in Northern Athletics Conference Semifinal game against Lakeland College (Feb. 19)...Netted nine points and grabbed six rebounds against Concordia University Ann Arbor (Jan. 25)...Scored eight points apiece in back-to-back games versus Dominican University (Jan. 19) and Lakeland College (Jan. 23). 2011-12 Season (Freshman): Did not appear in any games. High School (Pius XI): Named honorable mention all-conference in both basketball and football…Earned three varsity letters in basketball and two in football. Personal: Son of Mark and Mary Scholz…Has two younger brothers, Matthew and Michael.
